[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "Review identifies two genuine ERROR-severity API bugs that I verified against the source: (1) [38;5;10mADD state_history :history_event[0m UpdateExpression is invalid because DynamoDB's ADD action only supports Number and Set types, not List — confirmed across ~10 call sites in allocate_enrollments, dispatch_outreach, record_outreach_attempt, score_engagement, [3mpersist[23mdisenrollment, and process_disenrollment_decision; (2) the unreachable-terminal decrement in record_outreach_attempt references undefined [38;5;10m:zero[0m in ConditionExpression and passes [38;5;10mExpressionAttributeNames=None[0m, which would raise ValidationException — confirmed at the exact code location. The review provides concrete code-snippet fixes for both ERRORs ([38;5;10mSET state_history = list_append(if_not_exists(state_history, :empty), :history_event)[0m and the corrected update_item with [38;5;10m:zero[0m defined). It also includes a dedicated AWS SDK Accuracy table covering DynamoDB, Bedrock InvokeModel shape, Kinesis, CloudWatch, Athena, and SageMaker, a Healthcare-Specific Requirements section addressing PHI logging, synthetic-data labeling, Decimal-at-boundary discipline, tracking-ID privacy, Bedrock de-identification, cohort-feature sensitivity, and decision-supported disenrollment, plus 1 WARNING and 6 NOTEs each with severity ratings and actionable code fixes (CloudWatch present-with-None dimension trap, TCM fit-vs-inclusion field inconsistency, unused program_lookup parameter, brittle sentinel-condition validator, globals() mock comment, recommend_cross_program_transitions pseudocode deviation). A re-review checklist maps each finding to a verifiable action. The review meets all pass criteria."}